    "notes": "Detection focus: (1) process.executable matching AppData\\Roaming paths with scheduler-themed names is a strong signal — legitimate taskschd.exe lives in System32; (2) outbound TLS from non-browser, non-system processes on port 443 to external IPs on a DC is highly anomalous; (3) HKCU Run key written by the same process that made the outbound connection completes the T1133 + T1547.001 chain. Correlate all three events by process.pid 4872 for high-confidence detection. False positive caution: mstsc.exe RDP and svchost-parented taskschd.exe are common — exclude System32-resident, SYSTEM-owned scheduler binaries."
